The paper discusses the scalability of blockchain networks and analyzes their transactional throughput, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR), distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), distributed ledger technology (cs.DLT), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
